column5: Received an email today from Nakina. Sender said they did not expect to see open water till May 20. In middle of severe winter storm today.
Bad news. Frankly, I wonder if we'll see open water much before that in N. Wisconsin and Upper Michigan.
60 degree temps, rain, spring winds raise he77 with ice. Cross your fingers, it isn't over yet.
We had a blizzard and white out conditions in Carroll County Ohio on Tuesday with temps in the 30's. Cool yesterday and forecast for the weekend is temps in the 60/70's. Only in NE Ohio
Come on down to my neck of the woods. 85 degrees here yesterday and the water is nice and soft. Going on the hunt for walleye again next weekend. PjShorthorn
